cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper deals with the problem of 3D human pose estimation from 2D joints, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves the use of mixture density networks, which is a machine learning technique (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the issue of occluded joints, which is related to robotics and control (cs.RO). The use of multiple feasible hypotheses is a form of uncertainty modeling, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves the evaluation of the proposed approach on various datasets, which is related to graphics (cs.GR).
